&lt;p&gt;If you’ve ever run your fingers along a glossy window casing and thought, “There’s no way paint will stick to this,” you’re right—at least not for long without the right prep. I’ve walked into plenty of homes where a beautifully painted room is betrayed by peeling, nicked baseboards and door frames. The culprit is almost always the same: slippery, factory-smooth or oil-painted trim with zero mechanical bite. This is where trim sanding earns its keep. Done right, scuff sanding turns that slick plastic-like surface into a paint-friendly foundation that your primer and topcoat can lock onto.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/26.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/instagram/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/pinterest/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/12/23/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding/cards/facebook/how-to-scuff-sand-glossy-trim-for-better-adhesion-trim-sanding.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><readingTime>12</readingTime></item><item><title>Use Hard Backing Pads For Flat Panels</title><link>https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 27 Nov 2025 14:34:47 +0000</pubDate><category>Interface Pads &amp; Backing Pads</category><category>grit-100</category><category>grit-360</category><category>paint prep</category><description>Get pro-flat panels with hard backing pads. Learn when a sander interface pad helps, when it hurts, and how to sand dead flat without waves or swirls.</description><summary>&lt;h2 id="hard-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad-guide"&gt;Hard Pads for Flat Panels: Sander Interface Pad Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a certain hush that falls over the shop when a panel finally reads flat. The lights reflect in a clean, uninterrupted glide across the grain, and you can feel the promise of that finish under your fingertips. I remember a maple tabletop that fought me for three late nights. I had a soft pad on my sander, a foam disc, and the hope that “gentle” would keep me safe. Instead, the board smiled back at me with a washboard of highs and lows. Swirls near the edges, dipped corners, and a telegraphed glue line that wouldn’t die. The fix wasn’t more time; it was the right pad. I swapped to a hard backing pad, parked a sander interface pad for the profiles and inside corners, and the surface transformed—crisp, even, and ready to finish. That day, I stopped thinking of pads as accessories and started treating them like cutting tools.&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/images/brand/01.webp" medium="image"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/facebook/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/><media:content url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad.jpg" medium="image"/><media:thumbnail url="https://blog.equalle.com/posts/2025/11/27/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad/cards/instagram/use-hard-backing-pads-for-flat-panels-sander-interface-pad